    "created_at": "2016-06-08T01:33:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-06-08T01:33:36Z",
    "body": "This is a feature of OS X, it allows an app to enter fullscreen without sizing to the size of screen. As a neutral framework standing in the middle between users and the system, Electron should not prevent users from making use of a platform-specific feature, even though it is sometimes not expected.\n\nI'm closing this as won't fix.\n"
