    "created_at": "2016-07-07T09:21:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-07T09:21:09Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz I agree with your argument, but it would be nice if we could achieve the expected result without having to resort to dirty hacks like:\n\n``` js\nwin.on('enter-full-screen', () => {\n    win.setMaximumSize(2147483647, 2147483647);\n});\n```\n\nMaybe an option like `fullscreenFill`? That ignores maxWidth/maxHeight settings in fullscreen.\n"
